  "title": "SOFTWARE DEVELOPER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Develop and maintain Java and C++ applications to deliver robust software solutions aligned with business needs</li><li>Design and implement web applications using HTML/HTML5, JavaScript, and frameworks such as AngularJS, ExtJS, JQuery, and Bootstrap to enhance user experience and functionality</li><li>Interface with databases including MS SQL, Oracle, and MySQL using ODBC/JDBC and SQL to ensure efficient data management and retrieval</li><li>Architect and implement multi-tier software solutions to support scalable and maintainable systems</li><li>Apply object-oriented software design principles and create UML models to document and communicate system designs effectively</li><li>Utilize containerization technologies such as Docker to enable virtualization and streamline deployment processes</li><li>Develop and deploy applications and web services on commercial cloud platforms like AWS to ensure high availability and scalability</li><li>Implement AWS Lambda functions using Python or JavaScript to create serverless computing solutions that optimize resource usage</li><li>Integrate Single Sign-On (SSO) solutions including OAuth, OpenID Connect, and SAML to enhance security and user authentication processes</li><li>Establish secure communication protocols using MQ, MQTT, SFTP, and FTP-S to protect data transmission and maintain system integrity</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Engineering, Computer Science, or a relevant discipline</li><li>Minimum of 4-5 years of experience in software development and system integration</li><li>Demonstrated strong analytical and problem-solving skills applied to complex technical challenges</li><li>Proven ability to work resourcefully and collaboratively as a self-motivated team player</li></ul>",
